## Analysis Report: Infinite Query Patterns & Pagination Strategy

### 1. **ProfilePostCards.jsx - Exact Infinite Query Pattern**

**File:** `/c/Users/johnm/iskrib_v3/client/src/components/HomePage/postCards/ProfilePostCards/ProfilePostCards.jsx` (Lines 90-109)

```javascript
const {
    data,
    fetchNextPage,
    hasNextPage,
    isFetchingNextPage,
    isLoading,
} = useInfiniteQuery({
    queryKey: ['userJournals', user?.userData?.[0].id],
    queryFn: ({queryKey, pageParam}) => getUserJournals(pageParam, 5, queryKey[1], session?.access_token),
    getNextPageParam: (lastPage) =>{
        if(lastPage.hasMore){
            const lastJournal = lastPage?.data[lastPage?.data.length - 1];
            return new Date(lastJournal.created_at).toISOString();
        } else {
            return undefined;
        }
    },
    enabled: !!user?.userData?.[0].id,
    refetchOnWindowFocus: false,
})
```

**Key Pattern Details:**
- **queryFn signature:** `({queryKey, pageParam}) => getUserJournals(pageParam, 5, queryKey[1], session?.access_token)`
  - `pageParam` is the cursor (ISO timestamp on first load, undefined)
  - `queryKey[1]` contains the userId
  - Hardcoded page size: `5` items

- **getNextPageParam:** Returns `created_at` ISO string from the last journal if `hasMore` is true, otherwise undefined

- **Cursor Strategy:** `created_at` timestamp-based (ISO 8601 format). First page has `pageParam` as undefined.

- **Page Flattening (Line 293):**
  ```javascript
  const journals = data?.pages.flatMap((page) => page.data) || [];
  ```

- **IntersectionObserver Sentinel (Lines 29-31, 671, 281-286):**
  ```javascript
  const {ref, inView} = useInView({ threshold: 0.2 })

  // In return JSX (Line 671):
  <div ref={ref} className='in-view-container'>
      {isFetchingNextPage && (
          <MoonLoader loading={isFetchingNextPage} color="var(--loader-color)" size={20}/>
      )}
  </div>

  // Trigger fetching (Lines 281-286):
  useEffect(() =>{
      const isLoadingMore = isFetchingNextPage || !hasNextPage
      useEffect(() =>{
          if(inView && !isLoadingMore){
              fetchNextPage();
          }
      }, [fetchNextPage, isLoadingMore, inView])
  }, [data])
  ```

